This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language adversarial input generation for text classification models. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves learning a decoder for generation and attacking other existing models. Additionally, it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as adversarial attacks have been extensively studied in image classification tasks. Finally, it may also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as adversarial attacks are a common concern in security and privacy.
